table3.Title: 40 Winks
table3.Notes: Originally to be published by GT Interactive around late 1999 to early 2000 but canceled. The Nintendo 64 port was published by Piko Interactive in 2019 after being funded through Kickstarter.[18]

table3.Title: Dragon Sword
table3.Notes: Originally to be published by MGM Interactive but cancelled. The game is planned to be published by Piko Interactive.[19]

table3.Title: Glover 2
table3.Notes: Originally to be published by Hasbro Interactive around mid 1999 but cancelled. The game is planned to be published by Piko Interactive.[20]

table3.Title: R64
table3.Notes: A "playable album" consisting only of music and a 3D visualizer, it is one of several albums by German musician Remute designed to be played on older video game hardware.[21][22]

table3.Title: Xeno Crisis
table3.Notes: Published for eighth generation consoles, the game was ported to several retro consoles in 2023.
